00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:25,399
ARTHUR: To a beautiful wedding.

778
00:55:26,600 --> 00:55:27,999
I should go.

779
00:55:28,640 --> 00:55:30,153
-I should go soon.
-No, no, no, no.

780
00:55:30,240 --> 00:55:31,240
ARTHUR: No, you sit down.

781
00:55:31,840 --> 00:55:33,513
You don't want to be among women

782
00:55:33,600 --> 00:55:35,398
when there's a baby coming.
Have another.

783
00:55:35,480 --> 00:55:38,040
Do you think her husband will take
the same advice and stay away?

784
00:55:38,280 --> 00:55:40,556
JOHN: No, no, Freddie'll be there.

785
00:55:41,160 --> 00:55:42,798
Nothing'll keep him away.

786
00:55:42,880 --> 00:55:44,951
Tommy said it's all right
for him to be there.

787
00:55:45,360 --> 00:55:46,873
Isn't that right, Tommy?

788
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:49,037
That's right. I'm all heart tonight.

789
00:55:49,120 --> 00:55:50,120
[CLEARS THROAT]

790
00:55:54,320 --> 00:55:56,231
[LAUGHS] You know what, John?

791
00:55:57,320 --> 00:56:00,278
I think it's that lovely barmaid,

792
00:56:00,360 --> 00:56:02,476
that pretty barmaid
that just walked out,

793
00:56:02,560 --> 00:56:05,279
that's made our brother go all soft.

794
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:06,709
Drinks to that!

795
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:11,031
[INAUDIBLE]

796
00:56:22,760 --> 00:56:23,955
Ada!

797
00:56:28,200 --> 00:56:29,713
Come on, open up!

798
00:56:30,160 --> 00:56:31,230
[BABY CRYING]

799
00:56:33,800 --> 00:56:34,800
There you go, love.

800
00:56:40,120 --> 00:56:41,758
He's beautiful.

801
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:47,274
It's a boy, Freddie.

802
00:56:54,360 --> 00:56:56,510
It's a beautiful baby boy.

803
00:57:07,520 --> 00:57:08,749
There you go.

804
00:57:10,480 --> 00:57:11,914
Welcome to the world, Son.

805
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:15,954
-Welcome.
-[DOOR KNOCKING]

806
00:57:16,120 --> 00:57:17,474
Open up, Police!

807
00:57:17,920 --> 00:57:20,230
-[DOOR SLAMMING]
-Freddie?

808
00:57:20,520 --> 00:57:23,114
You can't come in here!
There's a baby that's just been born.

809
00:57:23,200 --> 00:57:24,376
ADA: Freddie!
POLLY: There's a baby!

810
00:57:24,400 --> 00:57:26,198
Don't do this here.

811
00:57:26,360 --> 00:57:27,998
Don't hurt him! Freddie!

812
00:57:28,080 --> 00:57:30,959
You're hurting him! Leave him alone!

813
00:57:31,200 --> 00:57:33,157
You're taking me away from my baby.

814
00:57:34,600 --> 00:57:36,352
-Ada!
-Freddie!

815
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:37,874
Ada!

816
00:57:46,160 --> 00:57:47,878
[MEN SINGING]

817
00:57:51,880 --> 00:57:54,599
You want me to open that champagne now?

818
00:57:54,760 --> 00:57:55,760
[DOORS SLAMMING]

819
00:57:56,920 --> 00:57:58,115
It's a boy.

820
00:58:00,920 --> 00:58:02,240
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

821
00:58:02,320 --> 00:58:04,152
ARTHUR: Oi, Polly! Polly!

822
00:58:04,800 --> 00:58:07,030
But the police came and
took his father away!

823
00:58:07,720 --> 00:58:09,870
Don't you dare look at me like that!

824
00:58:19,040 --> 00:58:20,040
[SPITS] You liar!

825
00:58:32,320 --> 00:58:33,320
[THEME SONG PLAYING]

826
00:58:49,440 --> 00:58:54,435
<i>♪ Take a little walk to the edge of town
and go across the track ♪</i>

